Time::Fuzzy
===========

Nobody will ever say "it's 11:57". People just say "it's noon". This
Perl module does just the same: it adds some human fuzziness to the way
computer deal with time.



INSTALLATION
============

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


Or, using Module::Builder:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install



SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION
=========================

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Time::Fuzzy

You can also look for information at:
  . Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Time-Fuzzy
  . CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Time-Fuzzy
  . AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Time-Fuzzy
  . CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Time-Fuzzy



